            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "NASA Science is a critical driver of American leadership and local economic activity. In CA-29, firms like Spectrolab, Inc. and Clay Lacy Aviation have received over $350,000 in NASA funding recently, supporting high-tech jobs and innovation. This $9 billion request ensures the U.S. remains competitive against China's space ambitions while stabilizing the skilled aerospace workforce that CA-29 contributes to.",
            "rationale": "Combines local spending data ($351,709.80 across Spectrolab and Clay Lacy Aviation) with strategic talking points regarding China and workforce stability.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
