            "draft_value": "* $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to restore funding levels and pursue National Academies' Decadal Survey priorities.\n* Supports local aerospace activity in CA-29, including contractors like Spectrolab, Inc. and Clay Lacy Aviation, Inc.\n* Secures U.S. leadership in space science to set exploration norms in the face of rising international competition.\n* Protects a critical STEM workforce that generates a 3:1 economic return on investment.",
